==English==
{{wikipedia}}
===Pronunciation===
*{{IPA|/ˈspiːdɹʌn/}}

===Etymology===
[[Portmanteau word]] of [[speed]] and [[run]].

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A play-through of a [[computer]] or [[video game]] in which the whole game or a select part of it, such as a single [[level]], is played with the intent of completing it as quickly as possible, optionally with certain [[prerequisite|prerequisites]].
#:''In the '''speedrun''' of [[w:Super Mario Bros. 3|Super Mario Bros. 3]], Richard Ureta finishes the whole [[video game|game]] in just 11 minutes.''
# One of multiple [[version|versions]] of such a play-through.
#:''The current world record of 11 minutes by Richard Ureta is much better than his older '''speedrun''' of 12 minutes.''

====Translations====
*Japanese: [[タイムアタック]]

===Verb===
{{en-infl-irreg|speedrun|speedruns|speedrunning|speedran|speedrun}}

# The act of creating a speedrun.
#:''In my most recent attempt to '''speedrun''' [[w:Super Mario Bros. 3|Super Mario Bros. 3]], I almost managed to [[beat]] Richard Ureta's [[record]].''

====Translations====
*Japanese: [[タイムアタック]]

